# Changelog

*Functional* changes to the public interface of Mnemonic Bytes will be listed here, by version. *Non-functional* changes may also be included, if they are particulary noteworthy or might impact developers using the library.

The format is based on [Keep a Changelog](https://keepachangelog.com/en/1.0.0/), and Mnemonic Bytes adheres to [Semantic Versioning](https://semver.org/spec/v2.0.0.html).

## 0.0.1 - 2022-11-21
### Added
- Added methods to encode and decode bytes in various formats to base-256 mnemonic phrases.

## 0.0.2 - 2022-11-21
### Changed
- Corrected links to repo and README.

## 0.0.3 - 2022-11-21
### Changed
- Change interface to `.encode` to use `Bufferable` and `ArrayBuffer` instead of a host of `TypedArray`s.
- Calls to `.encode` will now accept mixed-case values.
